</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5759368ABD6EFFFFF892F84CE8B2FED9" blockId="1.[136,778,1885,2093]" lastBlockId="1.[810,1452,158,365]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">
<emphasis id="6592EA98BD6EFFFFF892F84CEDFFF80B" bold="true" box="[189,427,1957,1983]" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Revised diagnosis.</emphasis>
First flagellomere thicker than following ones, longer than second flagellomere. Mesoscutellum relatively large. Forewing with SC well developed, with two branches (Sc1 and Sc2); M+Cu smoothly bent medially, ap-Cu vein absent; Rs+M twice longer than 1-M, 2-M slightly shorter than Rs+M; 3-Rs strongly arched; angle between 1-M and 1-Cu 
<emphasis id="6592EA98BD6EFFFFFD7FFF0EE93EFEB4" box="[1360,1386,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">ca</emphasis>
. 90°; cell 1R elongate (ratio length/ width = 
<quantity id="901E9B6FBD6EFFFFFCF8FEE3E955FE90" box="[1239,1281,266,292]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName id="90E64D09BD6EFFFFFD28FEE3E928FE90" authorityName="Rasnitsyn" authorityYear="1983" box="[1287,1404,266,292]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Tapholyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="174" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6592EA98BD6EFFFFFD28FEE3E928FE90" box="[1287,1404,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="174">Tapholyda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 4- Rs sub equal to 1-M; 2r-rs near apex of pterostigma, 3r-m oblique and inclined toward wing apex.
</paragraph>
